Neat, it has an example of the kind of thing Dijkstra was talking about when he wrote Go To Statement Considered Harmful.<p><pre><code>    main( ) {
      auto c;
    read:
      c= getchar();
      putchar(c);
      if(c != &#x27;*n&#x27;) goto read;
    }               &#x2F;* loop if not a newline *&#x2F;
</code></pre>
People forget the world of ubiquitous goto enabled control flow with languages like this and Dartmouth BASIC.
